page.title: 12BIRD SURVEY-Part two.
page.content: Bird sightings as follows: (*=sighted frequently,**=sighted only in the particular habitat). 1.COMMON *=Swallow,Meadow pipit,Rook, Blackheaded gull,Jackdaw,Crow,Skylark, Magpie. **=Wheatear. 2.BEACH *=Herring,Lesser and Greater Blackbacked and Blackheaded Gulls; Jackdaw,Dunlin,Oystercatcher,Shelduck. **=Shelduck,Dunlin,Heron,Redshank, Oystercatcher,Sandpiper,Cormorant. 3.FARMLAND *=Swallow,Blackheaded and Herring Gulls,Rook,Magpie,Starling, Jackdaw,Crow,Blackbird. **=Kingfisher. 4.ESTATE *=Pied wagtail,Jackdaw,Rook, House sparrow,Starling,Blackheaded and Herring Gulls,Robin,Blue and Great Tit Blackbird. **=Goldfinch,Collared Dove and House sparrow. BIRDS COMMON TO ALL 4 HABITATS=Jackdaw Rook,Crow,Pied Wagtail,Swallow,Herring and Blackheaded Gulls and Great Tit.
